name: NewYorker
text: Set in the early 2000s, somewhere in the Midwest, “Yes, God, Yes” is an incisive satire of religious repression. https://t.co/2UXE7DrP5v

name: NewYorker
text: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez’s rebuttal to Ted Yoho should be studied for its measured cadence, its artful construction, and its refusal of ugliness, David Remnick writes. https://t.co/U1EpZnPdhH
